N.B.
/on_select returns quote for each dynamic item component (i.e. base item(s) & customizations), as selected by the buyer, along with fulfillment level costs;
For each base item & customization, the quote includes:
Item price - total & unit price
Available & maximum quantity
Tax
For customizations, the above quote structure will also be a part of the payloads in /on_init, /on_confirm, /on_update, /on_cancel;
In case a customization is out-of-stock, the quantity should be 0 and the total price for the customization will be 0;
If anymandatory customization is out-of-stock or the required minimum quantity is not available, the buyer NP can prompt the buyer to select adifferent customization(for thesame customization groupand matching theveg/non-veg/eggtype of the original customization selected by buyer);
If anyoptional customization is out-of-stock or the quantity selected is not available, the quote should have thecustomization with the quantity available, but the base item and other customizations will have the quantity as selected by the buyer;
For all of the cases in 4 & 5 above,error.message in the response should have the list of corresponding item idsreferenced in stringified object notation, e.g. if base item "I1" for dynamic item "DI1" and customization "C15" for dynamic item "DI2" are both out of stock, error.message would be encoded as:"[{\"dynamic_item_id\":\"DI1\",\"item_id\":\"I1\",\"error\":\"40002\"}, {\"dynamic_item_id\":\"DI2\",\"customization_id\":\"C15\",\"customization_group_id\":\"CG3\",\"error\":\"40002\"}]". This is in addition to the error.code (40002) which is being sent by seller NP;
If there is a mismatch between the list of ids in 7 & the ids in quote with quantity less than requested or 7 is not honoured, the buyer NP can NACK /on_select with error code 22507;
5. Offers
Available offers may be a part of the catalog for the buyer NP to render:
Offers may be:
opt-in- buyer applies offer to their cart selection by entering offer id(s) prior to checkout;
auto-applied- offers are automatically applied;
As part of /select processing, SNP evaluates offers for which buyer is eligible (regardless of applicability of such offers) and sends details of these offers in /on_select;
provider will validate the offer id(s), for opt-in offers, and apply the offer(s) to the cart selection;
auto-applied offers will be shown in the offer quote. If buyer doesn’t want any auto-applied offer, they can remove the offer from the cart and buyer NP will communicate this to seller NP in /select, /init,  /confirm;
Handling of exception conditions for offers:
if offer is no longer valid in pre-order APIs such as /on_init or /on_confirm, seller NP can send error code 30006;
if offer is valid but cannot be fulfilled (e.g. offer item not available for offers such as freebie, etc.), seller NP can send error code 30007;
if offer is no longer valid or cannot be fulfilled in /on_confirm, seller NP should cancel the order;
