Rules for order confirmation
/confirm and /on_confirm calls should be idempotent;
Buyer NP will create the order id which will be unique across the network. In response to /confirm from buyer NP, seller NP sends /on_confirm with the same order_id;
Buyer NP (BNP) sends /confirm, Seller NP (SNP) validates[804]order:
if validation successful, SNP responds with ACK:
SNP creates order (preferably with internal state to indicate order is being processed), but shouldn’t forward to merchant for processing & fulfillment;
if validation not successful, SNP responds with NACK with error code31002(order validation failure):
after BNP receives NACK, they should cancel the order withreason code999 (order cancelled because of order confirmation failure);
if this order is passed in subsequent API calls (/confirm, /status, /cancel, /update, etc.), SNP returns NACK with error code 30018 (order not found);
SNP may also respond with NACK due to other internal errors (http 504, retriable error code31001):
BNP should retry[805]/confirm. If after the retry interval, BNP doesn’t receive ACK/NACK, they should cancel the order with reason code999;
if BNP doesn’t receive ACK/NACK or /on_confirm, they should retry /confirm (same as above). If within the retry interval, BNP doesn’t receive ACK/NACK or /on_confirm, they should cancel the order with reason code999;
SNP sends /on_confirm, BNP validates[806]order:
if validation successful, BNP responds with ACK:
SNP forwards order to merchant for processing & fulfillment;
if validation not successful, BNP responds with NACK with error code23002 (order validation failure):
after SNP receives NACK, they should cancel the order with reason code998 (order cancelled because of order confirmation failure)& push the status change to BNP;
if this order (with cancellation state & reason code) is passed in subsequent API calls (/on_confirm, /on_status, /on_cancel, /on_update), BNP responds with ACK;
BNP may also NACK due to internal errors (http 504/503, retriable error code23001):
SNP should retry[807]/on_confirm. If after the retry interval, SNP doesn’t receive ACK/NACK, they should cancel the order with reason code998;
If order is passed in subsequent API calls within the retry window (/status, /track, /cancel, /update), SNP responds with current order state along with error code 31003 to indicate order processing in progress;
If order is passed in subsequent API calls after cancellation (/status, /cancel, /update), SNP sends response with order state as cancelled;
If SNP doesn’t receive ACK/NACK for /on_confirm, they should retry /on_confirm. If after the retry interval, SNP doesn’t receive ACK/NACK, they should cancel the order with reason code998;
/update & /on_update
Scenario 1 -Part cancel by merchant
Cancel of item(s) can only be initiated if fulfillment state is "Pending";
A separate fulfillment is created for the cancellation and the item & quantity assigned to it. This fulfillment also has associated details such as cancellation reason code, quote trail;
Updated quote is provided by the seller NP at the refund trigger point ("Liquidated", "Return_Picked", "Cancelled") and the buyer NP can calculate the amount of refund from the quote trail;
