N.B.
A dynamic item comprises a base item and one or more customizations. The quantity of a dynamic item will be the same as the corresponding quantity for the base item and the quantity for customizations will be defined as per configuration of the customization group, for the customization. For part cancel of dynamic item for specific quantity, the base item and customizations should be cancelled in the same proportion and the quote updated accordingly:
e.g. for an order O1:
dynamic item (DI1) includes (item type, quantity):
I1 - 3
C1 - 3
C2 - 3
=> DI1 has qty 3 and each DI1 includes:
I1 - 1
C1 - 1
C2 - 1
(part cancel for 1 qty of DI1 should include the above and the quote / quote trail should be updated accordingly)
For customized product, seller NP needs to cancel the dynamic item and set the quantity & total price to 0 for all item & customization components;
Individual item or customization components can’t be part-cancelled;
If either of 1 or 2 is not followed, buyer NP should NACK the /on_update with error code 22508;
For merchant part-cancel, the buyer NP may sendNACK with error code 22501(if the buyer does not accept part fill for the order). In this case, the seller NP will be required to rollback this part cancel request and cancel the full order;
